                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/699.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 25, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>It has been finally decided by the diplomatic corps that ministers recommend to
                    their Governments to quietly increase legation guards to maximum under the
                    protocol, which would exercise moral restraint upon natives and substitute
                    cooperation for individual action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
